> These, friends, are not your average pork chops. Our chefs gave 'em a steak-like treatment, transforming the everyday protein into something above and beyond. The chops are seared to perfection, then drizzled with an ultra-savory, rosemary-flecked pan sauce. The sides? Just as impressive. We're serving up creamy mashed potatoes and roasted carrots and red onion wedges to round everything out.

== Roasted Veggies ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Toss carrots and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

While veggies roast, dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. (TIP: For a smoother texture, peel potatoes first.) Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot.

Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

== Beef Tenderloin ==

While potatoes cook, pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer beef to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, strip @rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have 2 tsp (3 tsp for 4 servings).

> Swap in beef or chicken for pork; cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side, or cook chicken until cooked through, 4-6 minutes per side.

== Rosemary Demi-Glace Pan Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for beef over medium heat. Add @red onion{}(minced) and chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring often, until onion is softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @chicken demi-glace{1} and ¼ cup water (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

== Mashed Potatoes Finish ==

Return pot with drained potatoes to medium-low heat. Add @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season generously with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Slice beef crosswise.

> Slice beef or chicken against the grain.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Divide beef, mashed potatoes, and veggies between plates. Top beef with sauce and serve.